<h2>Call for Papers</h2>

<p>With the advent of digital TV (such as the North American ATSC-DTV) and rapid advances in digital displays (such as LCDs and DLPs), research efforts toward the development of 3-D TV have taken on a new zeal.  This Special Session of  “3-D TV: Primed for Success?” will provide the community an encouraging and concrete vision of the not-too-distance future of advanced television and home theatre.  The goal is to establish a focus for discussion of the major research areas that are fundamental for the success of 3-D TV. Topics covered in this special session include but are not limited to::</p>

<ul>
  <li>Standard(s) for 3-D TV</li>
  <li>Human factors for 3-D TV</li>
  <li>3-D TV capture</li>
  <li>3-D TV system/transmission</li>
  <li>3-D TV display</li>
  <li>Content generation of 3-D TV</li>
  <li>IBusiness models for 3-D TV</li>
</ul>

